data.chText: 击退；驱逐
data.enText: to successfully fight sb who is attacking you, your country, etc. and drive them away

data.chText: 击退进攻 / 入侵；驱逐入侵者
部队挫败了对该岛南部的渗透企图。
data.enText: Troops repelled an attempt to infiltrate the south of the island.

data.chText: 这种爬行动物浑身是刺，几乎所有的捕食者都退避三舍。
data.enText: The reptile's prickly skin repels nearly all of its predators.

data.chText: 推开；赶走；驱除
data.enText: to drive, push or keep sth away

data.chText: 驱除昆虫的乳剂
这种织物进行过防水处理。
data.enText: The fabric has been treated to repel water.

data.chText: 使恐惧；使厌恶

before.enText: not used in the progressive tenses

data.enText: to make sb feel horror or disgust

data.chText: 这种气味让我恶心。
data.enText: I was repelled by the smell.

data.chText: 排斥；相斥
data.enText: if one thing repels another, or if two things repel each other, an electrical or magnetic force pushes them apart

data.chText: 同极相斥。

data.text: shock ♦ appal ♦ horrify ♦ disgust ♦ sicken ♦ repel ♦ revolt

data.chText: 以上各词均含使人震惊、惊愕之义。
data.enText: These words all mean to surprise and upset sb very much.

data.chText: 指使震惊、使惊愕：
data.enText: [often passive] to surprise sb, usually in a way that upsets them

data.chText: 听到他的死讯，我们都感到震惊。
data.enText: We were all shocked at the news of his death.

data.chText: 指使大为震惊、使惊骇：
data.enText: to shock and upset sb very much

data.chText: 罪行之残暴使公众大为震惊。
data.enText: The brutality of the crime has appalled the public.

data.chText: 指使惊吓、使惊恐、恐吓：
data.enText: to make sb feel extremely shocked, upset or frightened

data.chText: 全国都对这些凶杀案感到大为震惊。
data.enText: The whole country was horrified by the killings.

data.chText: 指使作呕、使厌恶、使反感：
data.enText: to make sb feel shocked and almost ill because sth is so unpleasant

data.chText: 影片中的暴力程度实在让我反感。
data.enText: The level of violence in the movie really disgusted me.

data.chText: 指使大为震惊、使愤怒、使作呕：
data.enText: ( BrE ) to make sb feel very shocked, angry and almost ill because sth is so unpleasant

data.chText: 公众看到这些充满暴力和死亡的画面大为震惊。
data.enText: The public is becoming sickened by these images of violence and death.

data.chText: 指使恶心、使厌恶：
data.enText: [often passive] ( rather formal ) to make sb feel rather disgusted

data.chText: 他呼吸中的酒精气味让我恶心。
data.enText: I was repelled by the smell of drink on his breath.

data.chText: 指使恶心、使厌恶：
电影里的各种暴力场面令我非常反感。
data.enText: All the violence in the movie revolted me.

data.chText: 用disgust、repel还是revolt？
disgust和revolt语气较repel强烈，尤其因道德而非身体方面的原因；对某人的观点或个人品质感到厌恶可用repel，但如果这些观点或品质变成行动，用repel语气就不够强烈：
data.enText: Disgust and revolt are stronger than repel , especially when the reason is moral, not physical. You might be repelled by sb's opinions or personal qualities, but if these opinions or qualities lead to action, repel may not be strong enough.

simple_means.memory_skill: re 反 + pel 驱动；推 → 推回去 → 击退

tr: cause to move back by force or influence
example: push back the urge to smoke

value.def: When an army repels an attack, they successfully fight and drive back soldiers from another army who have attacked them.

example.ex: They have fifty thousand troops along the border ready to repel any attack.
example.tran: 他们有5万人的部队驻扎在边境，随时准备击退任何进攻。

value.def: When a magnetic pole repels another magnetic pole, it gives out a force that pushes the other pole away. You can also say that two magnetic poles repel each other or that they repel .

example.ex: Like poles repel, unlike poles attract...
As these electrons are negatively charged they will attempt to repel each other.
example.tran: 因为这些电子都是带负电荷的，它们会互相排斥。

value.def: If something repels you, you find it horrible and disgusting.

example.ex: ...a violent excitement that frightened and repelled her.
example.tran: 使她恐惧和厌恶的强烈兴奋感

example.ex: She was very striking but in some way I felt repelled.
example.tran: 她非常引人注目，但我觉得她有些讨厌。
